pull.title: CWallet: fix mapAddress book update
pull.body:
Fix update of internal data structure (mapAddressBook) after changes to the address book, and add convenience methods EraseAddressBookName, GetDefaultAddress, SetDefaultAddress to be used from UI.

The problem was introduced in the new CWallet class; mapAddress book used to be updated in db.cpp. It now makes more sense to do the update directly in CWallet.

repo.name: bitcoin

events.message: Fix update of internal data structure (mapAddressBook) and add methods EraseAddressBookName, GetDefaultAddress, SetDefaultAddress

events.body: hm right, seems that I did some duplicated effort :-)

Your Erase naming is more consistent with the name of other functions.
SetDefaultAddress was missing.
Also, I agree that code should be extracted from .h to .cpp files!

It's nice to see some activity, and thanks for the (indirect) feedback! :-)
If this is still relevant with the new QT GUI, please rebase and re-open.
For the record, this fix got merged for 0.3.24.
